  "texts": [
    "Influence of PD Approaches and Moderating Factors on STEM Teaching Outcomes.",
    "The analysis of 31 studies on STEM education professional development in China identified key factors that consistently affect project outcomes.",
    "While the specific predictors or moderating variables such as project duration, teacher experience, or region within China are not uniformly detailed across all the studies, some recurring themes and factors emerge as influencing the effectiveness of these PD initiatives.",
    "Improving teachers' self-efficacy, particularly in interdisciplinary communication, enhances their confidence and directly impacts their teaching practices.",
    "Teachers with higher self-efficacy are likelier to adopt innovative teaching strategies, leading to improved student engagement and better learning outcomes in STEM subjects."
  ],
